This time a touch shorter, Elgar pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Full and outside off, punched towards cover.
On the pads of Elgar, he looks to tuck it towards the leg side but it goes towards mid off off the leading edge of his bat.
Floated just outside off, Elgar pushes this one towards cover.
Ashwin has a change of ends also!
Umpires have called for the light meter to check for bad light. They look to continue as off now!
Full ball tossed up just outside off, de Bruyn blocks this one out off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone by de Bruyn.
On middle and off this time, Elgar flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Elgar flicks this one towards the leg side.
Another one on a similar line, Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Darted just outside off, Elgar defends it towards the leg side.
Jadeja has a change of ends!
Length ball just outside off, Shami gets it to shape back in just a bit. De Bruyn is confident where his stumps are and he makes a good leave.
Good length ball just outside off, de Bruyn blocks it out off the back foot back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle and off, de Bruyn blocks it out back towards Shami.
Floodlights are on now!
Another one fullish around off, pushed towards mid on by de Bruyn.
Good length ball on middle and leg, de Bruyn pushes this towards mid on.
Length ball outside off to start off, de Bruyn looks to play at it but misses as he does so inside the line of the delivery.
Mohammad Shami comes back into the attack! He has bowled only one over so far which was a maiden.
Tossed up just outside off, Elgar looks push at it but it goes off the outside edge towards short third man.
Tossed up on middle and off, Elgar has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Elgar defends this one by presenting the full face of the bat.
Elgar blocks this one out nicely off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg.
Floated just outside off, Elgar manages to keep this one down by defending this off the front foot.
Mohammad Shami was supposed to bowl but Kohli seeing the left-hander on strike gives the ball back to Ashwin!
Pitching just outside off and turning away, de Bruyn pushes this one towards point.
Jadeja bowls this one on the middle pole line, de Bruyn pushes it back to Jadeja.
On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Darted just outside off, from round the wicket, Elgar defends this towards the leg side.
SIX! What a shot! Counter-attack! Full and floated just outside off, Elgar comes down the track and smashes this one over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Floated just outside off, Elgar pushes this towards mid on.
De Bruyn has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Ashwin bowls this one on middle and off, de Bruyn defends this one out.
Short and outside off, de Bruyn cuts this one off the back foot but Pujara at point dives to his right and saves at least a couple. Superb fielding.
De Bruyn plays that one off the front foot and into the ground.
Another one, shortish, de Bruyn pushes this towards mid on.
Tossed up just outside off, de Bruyn blocks it out from within the crease.
Floated ball on middle, Elgar flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dean flicks it towards mid on.
The batsman has driven it through mid-on.
Flighted delivery on off, Elgar comes down the track and tries to loft it but gets an outside edge past the point fielder for a couple. Lucky for Elgar here. No need to play that shot.
Full delivery on off, Elgar prods forward and defends this towards the off side.
FOUR! Outside off, de Bruyn gets down on one knee and reverse sweeps this one through backward point for a boundary. Misses the gully fielder by a whisker who gets out of the way of the delivery.
De Bruyn plays that one off the front foot and into the ground.

Loud appeal for LBW turned down by the umpire. Ashwin pitches this just outside off, it turns back in. De Bruyn looks to defend but misses to get hit on the back pad. The Indian players put in a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They think that the impact is outside off and thus they do not go for the review. Ball Tracker comes in and shows that they were right.
Beauty by Ashwin! Full and tossed up, de Bruyn looks to come forward and defend it but misses the ball completely as Saha gathers it.
Full and just outside off, de Bruyn works it towards the leg side.
Theunis de Bruyn is the new man in!

OUT! BOWLED! Excellent bowling from Ashwin! Markram's struggle in the subcontinent continues! Flighted ball on off, spinning into the batsman, Markram looks to defend but it goes between the bat and pad and disturbs the stumps. The replay shows that it brushed his front pad on its way. Early wicket for India and they would be looking to make further inroads before the end of day's play.
On the pads, Elgar works it down the leg side.

On the pads of Elgar, he flicks it towards square leg. Aiden sets off for a run but Elgar denies it and sets him down the river. Pujara tries to run in and gather the ball but fumbles. He still has a shy at the non-striker's end but Markram has dived in by then and is safe.
Full on middle and off, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Full and wide on off, pushed towards mid-wicket. Pressure building.
Similar ball, again pushed towards mid on.
Darted just outside off, pushed towards mid on.
On middle and off, blocked out onto the pitch.
On the pads of Markram, he flicks it towards square leg but straight to the man.
Markram defends this one off the front foot presenting the full face of the bat.
Shortish on middle and off, blocked off the back foot by Aiden.
On the pads, Elgar flicks it towards square leg for one.
Full and floated on off, Elgar does well to block it out.
Markram looks to defend this one but it goes off the leading edge towards point.
Aiden has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shortish this time, Markram blocks this one off the back foot.
Full and outside off, blocked out by Markram towards the off side.
Markram has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR! Bad start by Jadeja! Short and wide outside off, Markram goes onto the back foot and smashes it through point for a boundary.
Ravindra Jadeja comes into the attack!
Last ball of the over, Elgar defends this one off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Elgar punches this one off the back foot.
Full and wide outside off, Markram pushes it towards cover for a single. Markram is off the mark with that single.
Beaten! This time Ashwin pitches this one just outside off, it turns back in sharply. Markram looks to push but it tears him in half as it goes between his bat and pad.
Another similar delivery, Markram again blocks it out.
Full and flat on middle, Aiden blocks it out.
Spin time! Ravichandran Ashwin is into the attack now. He starts with a slip, leg slip, short leg and a gully in place. Attacking field-set this from India.

FOUR! Poor bowling from Ishant here! Strays down the leg side again does Sharma. Elgar just helps it on its way towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Spoiled what was turning out to be a good over.
Good length delivery on middle, Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.
Full delivery around off, Elgar pushes this to mid off for nothing.
Good length delivery on middle, Dean defends it out towards cover.
BEATEN! Brilliant delivery from Ishant! Bowls a full delivery outside off tempting Elgar to drive but he fails to put any bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar lets it go to the keeper.
On a length on middle, Markram defends it off the back foot. Maiden over to start off from Shami.
Good length delivery on off, Markram lunges forward and defends it towards mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Markram shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Aiden defends this off the back foot towards the leg side.
Full delivery on the pads, Aiden flicks it nicely but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Full delivery outside off, Markram lets the ball go to the keeper.
Mohammed Shami to bowl from the other end for the hosts.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ishant this time! Strays down the leg side, Elgar flicks this nicely towards the backward square leg region for a boundary. South Africa are underway.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Elgar defends it off the back foot towards the bowler.
On a length outside off, Dean lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Starts with a good length ball outside off, Elgar defends this out off the front foot.

Now then, 13 overs to go before the close of today's play. South Africa will hope to get through the nervy period unscathed. India, on the other hand, will be eager to get at least a couple of wickets. Join us in a while for an important passage of play.

The South African bowlers once again weren't upto the mark. The spinners especially, both Maharaj and Piedt went for over 100 runs and that too with a high economy rate. Philander was top class as he bowled very economically. Rabada too was decent but it were the spinners who disappointed.

INDIA HAVE DECLARED! They give South Africa a massive target of 395. One just feels they have batted South Africa out of the game. Once again it was the Rohit Sharma show in this innings. He notched up another ton. The Indian innings began slowly but then in the second and the third sessions, they really stepped on the gas. Scored at will. A total of 14 sixes were hit out of which 7 were hit by the Hitman. There were handy contributions from Pujara and Jadeja too but it was the opener who was the star.

FOUR! Short on middle and leg, Kohli powers the ball to the mid-wicket boundary. As this act is completed, he turns around from the non striker's end and calls out to Rahane to join him back to the hut as they've declared. The second innings tally is 323/4. The total target for the visitors to chase is 395.
Played to the point region by the batsman. One run added to the total.

Now that's absurd! Banged in short, around off, Rahane pulls but misses. De Kock holds the ball above his head but as he lands from his jump he tumbles and in the process, throws the ball out of his grasp
Yorker length on middle, Rahane has to scoop it out and they run one as the long off fielder mops up.
The ball is way wide on the leg side but Rahane still goes after it and misses.
Good length very wide outside off, Rahane flays his flat bat at it and misses.
Short ball outside off, Rahane cuts it towards the cover region.
Flighted ball on the pads, Kohli moves towards the leg side and plays it towards point for a single.
The batsman has played the reverse sweep. They pick up a single.
Flighted ball outside off, Rahane attempts to reverse sweep it but fails to put any bat on it.
SIX! What a shot from Rahane! He is doing a wonderful job so far. Flighted ball on middle, Rahane moves towards the leg side and lofts it over the extra cover region for a maximum.
Flighted ball on middle, Kohli flicks it towards the leg side for a single.
The umpires are checking for bad light! They are fine to continue at the moment.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Another edge, another FOUR! Fuller on off, Rahane yet again edges it and this time de Kock misfields. The ball then races to the boundary.
Back of a length on middle. Rahane misses his pull shot and de Kock makes a good save.
The batsman was beaten and missed the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Edges and four! But how? Too full outside off, Rahane plays inside the line of the ball, it takes a thickish edge and drags it to Faf at a widish first slip. The Protean skipper misfields and concedes a boundary.
A single as this is worked towards mid on. So the change of ends does not make a difference for the spinner. He continues leaking runs. 14 from this over.

FOUR! The paddle sweep the last time and the reverse sweep this time. Cheeky, cheeky stuff from Rahane. Also, he plays it with the back of the bat and down to the third man fence for another boundary.
FOUR! Cheeky! Out comes the paddle sweep and Rahane plays it well. It races away to the fine leg fence and bags a boundary.
Floats it up on off, Rahane looks to go inside out over covers but hits it a little too straight so only two taken.
The batsman plays a pull shot to this short delivery. One run added to the total.

In the air... safe! The change of ends almost worked for the spinner. This is floated outside leg. Kohli looks to whip it but it turns away. It goes off the leading edge towards wide long off, lands safe and two is taken.
The light meter is out and the umpire is seen to be taking a reading. It seems fine though for now. Also, change of ends for Keshav Maharaj.
An appeal but not given! This starts around off and then tails back in. Rahane looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. It seems to be going down leg.
Ajinkya Rahane is the new man in.

OUT! Gone in the process to up the scoring rate. Pitches it too full on middle and off, Jadeja looks to have a hoick somewhere on the on side. He misses it. The ball cracks open the woodwork. The dejected southpaw trots back and Kohli pats him on the shoulder for a quickfire 40. First wicket for Rabada in this Test match.
On the pads, tuned to the on side. No run.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli Stretched for it and floats it to deep point for a single.
on full on middle and off, Kohli turns it to mid-wicket for none.
On middle and leg, Kohli plays it to mid on. No run.
Faf du Plessis has turned to the pacer. He needs the run-flow to stop here.
Kagiso Rabada is on now!
Flatter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman. They pick up a single.
SIX! High and handsome! Piedt once again gives it air but it is little too full, just where Jadeja likes it. Ravindra tonks it over the long on fence for a biggie. DP also now has conceded over 100.
This is flatter and on the pads, the batsman works it through mid-wicket. He calls for two and takes it.
Slower but shorter outside off, Jadeja slaps it through covers and takes two.
SIX! Straight down the ground! Jadeja is the man to do so this time. This is full, right in the zone of Jadeja. He hammers it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Turns this towards mid-wicket. No run.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
FOUR! Slapped! 10 runs in two balls! This is wide and full outside off, Kohli hits it with brutal force and through covers. No chance for the fielder in the deep.
SIX! For the second time in the game, Maharaj concedes over 100 runs. Tossed on middle and off, Kohli slog sweeps this over the mid-wicket fence for half a dozen.
Drives and drives well towards Elgar at long off. Dean runs to his left and concedes two.
Floated on middle and off, Jadeja turns it off his pads to square leg for a single.

DRINKS! The lead is now 25 short of 350 and India have stepped on the gas here. The question is how much more will they want to add? South Africa on the other hand, can only try and pick wickets or stop the runs so that the declaration is delayed.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads this time. Kohli flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Gets in the line of the delivery and defends on the back foot.
The batsman has picked it early and slogged it through the leg side. They pick up a single.
Looks to cut the ball to the off side, he bottom edges it into the pitch.
Almost in the blockhole by Piedt. Jadeja had to dig it out and back to the bowler.
MISFIELD AND FOUR! Loopy ball outside off, Kohli smashes it towards cover. It bounces just in front of him, the fielder fails to stop it and goes behind to the fence.
Very full and outside off, Jadeja smashes it down towards long off for one.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. They pick up a single.
Nicely played in the end! Jadeja comes down the track, the bowler bowls it short. There is extra bounce. Jadeja does well to adjust and guides it through point for one.
Flatter and on middle, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on the pads, this is worked past the diving fielder at short fine leg for two.
Kohli has played it towards mid-wicket.
Takes the ball on the full and play it through mid on for a single.
That was close. Just on off, the southpaw goes on the back foot and gets a bottom edge on that. The ball bounces very close to the off stump.
On middle and leg, Jadeja clips it off his pads, to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Comes on the front foot and plays the ball towards mid off.
Floated on off. Played to long on for a single.
Kohli is off the mark! This is tossed up outside off, it is driven through covers for one.
Captain Kohli walks out to bat.

OUT! STUMPED! For the second time in the game Rohit Sharma has been stumped. End of another excellent knock. It is such a good innings that even the South Africa players run up to him and congratulate him as he walks back. The Indian pavilion and the crowd are on its feet to give him a standing ovation. He perishes in the attempt to hit a 14th biggie. Comes down the track and swings against the turn. He misses it and de Kock behind makes no mistake. India are effectively 310 for 3.
Flatter and on off, Jadeja works it towards mid-wicket for one.
This is on middle, Rohit brings the sweep shot out. It goes off the top edge but lands safe in the deep square leg region. A single taken.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shorter and outside off, Jadeja reaches out for it. He somehow gets bat to ball but places it wide of the fielder at deep point. The man there runs to his left, dives and saves a run for his side.

SIX! Three in a row! The lead is now over 300. This time Rohit comes down the track but does not quite get to the pitch of the ball. He still goes ahead with the shot, hits it with the turn and clears the long on fence with ease.
SIX! Pulls the length back on this one. Sharma greets it with a flat-batted slap to send the ball flying over mid-wicket for a flat six.
SIX! Tossed up on middle and off, Sharma charges to the pitch of the ball, and launches it wide to the left of the sweeper at long on for a maximum.
Full on middle and off, Jadeja comes down the track and lobs it to long off for a single.
Appeal for leg before but not given. Floated  on middle and leg. Ravindra looks to drive but misses. It hits him on the back pad but  it was probably down leg.
Tossed on middle and leg, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
A single to end! Flatter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for one.
Maharaj fires this on the pads, Jadeja looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Outside off, this is quicker again. Rohit looks to cut but gets an inside edge which goes towards fine leg for one.
That stays low! Quicker again and on middle, this one stays low. Rohit does well to get his bat down in time and keep it out.
Slower through the air outside off, Rohit looks to sweep but is done in by the slowness. He misses to get hit on the pads.
Shorter but quicker outside off, Jadeja goes back and mistimes his cut through covers. He takes the first one slowly but mid-way realizes there is a chance for a second but then Rohit refuses.
Keshav Maharaj is back!
Rohit shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Beaten! Short and wide outside off, Rohit goes for the cut but misses.
Shortish just outside off, Jadeja cuts it towards point for a single.
Full ball on the pads, driven towards the mid on region for a single.
FOUR! Bad line by Piedt and punished by Sharma. Sliding down the leg side, Sharma paddles it towards fine leg and the ball races to the fence.
Floated on middle and off, Sharma defends it from within the crease.

NOT OUT! Good decision by the umpire! Good length ball on middle, Jadeja attempts to defend but gets hit on the pads. The South African players appeal but nothing from the umpire. Philander wants the review and they go for it. The replays roll in and the ball was very close to the bat but Ultra Edge shows that it is pad first. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the impact was outside off and missing the off stump. Poor review from South Africa and they have lost their review.
Review time! Ravindra Jadeja is the man in question for an LBW. Looks to be hitting the pad outside the off stump line.

CENTURY! Back-to Back centuries for Rohit Sharma! What a match he is having. Century in the first innings and now in the second. Good length delivery on middle, Rohit flicks it towards the leg side for a single. He celebrates by raising his bat and soaks in the applause.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Jadeja flicks it towards the fine leg region for a single.

Good length ball on off which kept a little low, Rohit gets a toe end while defending it and it rolls towards short third man for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Moves to 99 does Rohit.
Good length ball down the leg side, Rohit attempts to flick but misses. QdK makes an excellent take behind the stumps.
FOUR! Brilliantly played! Moves on to 98 with that shot! Short ball outside off, Rohit drives this nicely past the cover fielder for a boundary.
Jadeja looks to reverse sweep this one but misses it completely.
SIX! Sir Jadeja in action as soon as he comes in! Tossed up outside off, Jadeja gets down on one knee and slog sweeps it over mid-wicket for a maxiumum.
Jadeja drives this one straight down the ground.
Jadeja has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Another one pitching outside leg, Sharma goes for the reverse sweep and it goes off the bottom half of his bat towards cover-point. The batters take a quick single. The fielder goes for the direct hit at the striker's end but misses.
Tossed up just outside leg, Sharma blocks this one out.
Ravindra Jadeja is the next man in. Maybe time for some power-hitting by the Indians!

OUT! Waste of a review from Pujara! That looked plumb on naked eye. Pujara has to go! Good length ball on middle, Pujara looks to defend but gets hit flush on the back pad. Vernon Philander does not even wait for the decision and the umpire agrees as he gives it out. Pujara consults with his partner and decides to go for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows no bat. Ball Tracker also rolls in and it is three reds as it is going on to hit the off stump. Pujara has to depart. He probably was looking to get to his century and that's why he may have went for the review.

Review time! This looks plumb to the naked eye but India have still gone for the review. Pujara is the man in question for an LBW, it has hit him on the back pad and the umpire has given him out. Let's see what the decision is...
Good length ball outside off, Rohit guides this towards the point region for a quick single.
Good length delivery on middle, Rohit defends it out.
Good length delivery on middle jagging back in, Sharma looks to flick it but hits the thigh pad and rolls towards square leg.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma pushes it towards mid on for nothing.
Full delivery outside off, Rohit drives this nicely towards the cover region for a brace. Bavuma chases after it and makes a clean sliding stop.
On off, Pujara dances down the track and defends it out.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
SIX! Excellent shot! A short delivery from Piedt and Pujara rocks back and pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a maximum.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara pushes it towards the leg side.
Flighted ball on off, Sharma defends it towards the point region for a single.
FOUR! Good shot from Rohit! Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Rohit pulls this nicely towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. First boundary after the Tea break.
Dane Piedt to continue from the other end after the Tea break.
Fullish delivery on middle, Pujara defends this out to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Pujara lets this ball go to the keeper who is standing up to the stumps.
We can see on the screen that Ravindra Jadeja is padded up! Time for some T20 style batting maybe?
Full delivery on middle, Pujara drives this towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Pujara attempts to defend but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards the leg side.
On a length outside off, Sharma pushes it towards the cover region for a single. First runs of the session.
Good length delivery on middle, Sharma defends it out to the bowler.

We are back for the final session of Day 4! Rohit Sharma and Cheteshwar Pujara make their way out to the middle. The South African players also make their way out to the middle. Wonder how long will the Indians bat before declaring. Vernon Philander will start the proceedings for the visitors.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

South Africa were poor with the ball and they had no answer as to how to bowl to Rohit and Pujara once they started to attack. Not only bowling, they were also poor in their fielding efforts and dropped a couple of chances. They look down and out and are in search of a spark to have any chance of making a comeback in the Test. Another intriguing session awaits. Join us at 1501 local (0931 GMT) for the final session.

The hosts started cautiously after the fall of Mayank's wicket but Rohit Sharma and Cheteshwar Pujara started to counter-attack. Pujara was excellent and roared back to form with a fantastic half-century along with Rohit, who has continued from where he left off in the first innings.
A session which has belonged to India!  They have not lost a wicket in this session and have added 140 runs.

NOT OUT! Pujara survives! Piedt floats this one a touch short and around off. Pujara comes down the track to reach to the pitch of the ball and tries to block it. He fails to do so and the South African players appeal in unison. The umpire is unmoved and the South African players mull over taking the review. Faf du Plessis eventually does go for the review and the umpire takes it upstairs. Ultra Edge comes in and shows that no bat is involved. Ball Tracker comes in now and shows that the impact is umpire's call. Pujara stays intact and South Africa do not lose their review as well. An eventful last ball and that will be TEA ON DAY 4!
Review time! South Africa have gone up for an LBW review against Cheteshwar Pujara. It looks close and let us see what will happen.
FOUR BYES! This one has gone down the leg side, it bounces a touch more than expected. De Kock gets a hand to it but is not able to stop it from going to the fine leg fence.
Fuller one outside off, driven towards mid on.
Flatter on middle and leg, Pujara pushes this onto the pitch and the ball rolls towards the leg side.
Tossed up on the boots of Pujara, he flicks this one towards mid on.
Pujara comes a touch down the track and pushes this one onto the ground.
Dane Piedt is back into the attack!
Sharma  has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball on middle and off, Sharma has punched the ball off the back foot.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

On the pads of Pujara, he clips this one towards square leg and sets off. He wants the second run but is sent back by Rohit. This also brings up the 150-run stand between these two. They have lead the hosts to a very comfortable lead and will be looking to end the session with their wickets still intact.
Floated again on middle and off, this time Sharma drives this powerfully past the bowler. Maharaj from mid on runs and dives to his left to keep it down to just a single.
Full and floated on off, Sharma pushes this one towards short mid-wicket.
Vernon Philander is back into the attack. His figures read 8-5-8-0.
Sharma pushes this one wide of long om for a single. He retains strike for the next over.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads of Sharma, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Sharma! Sharma opens the face of his blade and guides this down to third man for a boundary. Sharma taking the attack to the opposition now.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Sharma cuts it towards point and the ball has crossed the fence in a jiffy.
Flatter and on middle, Sharma has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another length ball outside off, Pujara opens the face of the bat and guides this one towards the man at gully.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, Pujara cuts this one through backward point and it races to the fence. With this boundary, he overtakes Rohit in the scoring charts. At least for now!
Length ball just outside off, Pujara looks to fend at it but misses as he plays inside the line. It goes to de Kock on the bounce.
Length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to let that one through.
Another length ball outside off, CP leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Shortish and outside off, Pujara cuts it towards point and takes a single.
Pujara gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks this out.
FOUR! On the pads this one, Pujara just flicks this down to fine leg and the ball races to the boundary. Bavuma gives this a chase but in vain.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Pujara pushes this one towards point off the front foot.
Full and floated on the pads, pushed towards long on and the batters take one.
Keshav Maharaj into the attack now.
FOUR BYES! Down the leg side this. Pujara looks to flick but misses. The ball goes way down the leg side and into the fine leg fence.
Pujara opens the face of his bat and guides this towards backward point.

OUCH! That must have hit Pujara hard! Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Pujara looks to block but misses. The ball crashes into his chest area and then rolls towards the third man region. Luckily for Pujara, no harm done.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards mid off for a single by Sharma.
On the pads, Sharma looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side as the ball rolls towards square leg. Sharma wanted the run but is sent back by Pujara.
Good length ball just outside off, pushed towards cover by Sharma.
Pujara shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and floated outside off, driven superbly towards the cover region for a single.

FOUR! Maybe Sharma should play in his natural avatar only! Short this time on middle, Sharma rocks back and smashes this over mid-wicket for a boundary. He did not time that too well and that is why it goes into the fence on the bounce.
This time the ball bounces high off the turf, Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the splice of the bat towards the empty gully region.
Pitches outside off and straightens, Sharma leaves it alone.
Flatter one just outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Fuller and just outside off, pushed to the cover region by CP.
Length ball on middle, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
South Africa have brought in a first slip now!

EDGED AND FOUR! Almost an action replay of the last chance. Length ball just outside off, it pitches and nips away. Pujara edges it and the ball goes between de Kock and Faf du Plessis at wide first slip through to the third man fence. If the first slip was available, this would have gone straight down this throat.
Length ball outside off, cut to the man backward point.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky for Pujara! Good length delivery outside off, Pujara attempts to defend but gets an edge which goes in between the keeper and wide of first slip. The ball rolls onto the third man fence. De Kock dived in an attempt to take the catch but does not reach it. The skipper looks to heavens to show his displeasure.
Good length delivery on off, Cheteshwar defends it off the front foot towards the off side.

Pujara comes down the track and flicks this one towards mid-wicket. The ball does not have the legs to get to the fence and the fielder does the mopping up job as the batters take three. India now effectively 201/1.
On the pads, Pujara flicks it towards the leg side.
Shortish this time, Pujara gets on the back foot and blocks it out.
Outside off, Pujara lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Flatter one on the pads, pushed towards long on for a single.

FOUR! Welcome to the attack, Senuran Muthusamy! Full and flatter just outside off, Rohit gets down on one knee and paddles it fine towards the leg side for a boundary. Rohit Sharma did not run at first but later as he saw that there was the fine leg fielder chasing the ball, he started jogging towards the other end. Does not matter as it has crossed the fence.
Senuran Muthusamy comes into the attack for the first time in this innings.
Full and on the pads, Sharma flicks it towards square leg and takes a single to retain strike.
Length ball on middle and off, Rabada defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara pushes this towards point and takes a single. This brings up the 100-run stand between Sharma and Pujara.

FOUR! Pujara gets to his 21st Test fifty with a glorious shot! Full ball outside off, Pujara leans into the drive and just creams it through the cover region. He has accelerated very well here to meet the demands of his team.
Bouncer just outside off, Pujara sways away from it.
Good length ball just outside off, Pujara pushes this towards point and sets off for a run but is sent back. Pujara might be in a hurry to get to his half century

DRINKS! Its time for the second drinks session in this extended session. After the slow start in the first half, India have started making a move on and are attacking the bowlers. They have added 53 more runs since the last drinks break and are looking in complete control. South Africa need wickets and that too quickly to have a slight chance to make a comeback into the game. Floodlights have also come on as it has gone slightly dark around the stadium.
Shortish ball just outside off, Sharma plays it late but straight to short third man.
On the pads, Pujara works it down to square leg and takes a single.
Pujara blocks out this one off the front foot onto the pitch.
Pujara defends this one off the front foot and blocks it out.
Sharma opens the face of his bat and guides this one smartly down to third man.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Length ball outside off, CP defends it from within the crease.

A loud appeal for a caught behind from South Africa but denied by the umpire. Rabada walks upto Pujara and jokingly asks Pujara whether he has edged but he does not respond. Length ball just outside off, it jags back in. Pujara looks to defend but he fails to do so. South African players appeal loudly for a caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. The visiting players mull over taking the review but opt against it. Ultra Edge later confirms that the ball had come off the back thigh pad. Good decision not to review this one.
Pujara pushes this fuller one outside off towards cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara plays it towards point.
Pujara stays in his crease and blocks this one out.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Last ball of the over, Sharma blocks this one out by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUCH! A quick run by the Indian batters but de Kock has been hurt by Bavuma's throw. Pujara pushes this with soft hands towards extra cover and sets off for a run. Sharma obliges and gets to the other end. Bavuma has a shy at the striker's end but misses. De Kock in an attempt to collect it gets hit on his right thumb. However, he looks alright and will continue.
Defended off the front foot by CP presenting the full face of the bat.
Touch fuller on middle, Pujara pushes it back towards the bowler.
Another similar delivery on middle, blocked out by Pujara.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Pujara tucks it towards  fine leg but finds the man.
Keshav Maharaj, the only wicket taker in this innings comes into the attack. He replaces Dane Piedt who has gone off the field.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, RS drives towards covers for a single.
BEATEN! Rohit seems to lose concentration here! Good length ball outside off, Rohit attempts to punch it off his back foot but fails to put any bat on it. He did not need to play that shot.
Full delivery on off, Rohit attempts to drive but it hits the inside half of his bat and it rolls onto his boot. It rolls onto the pitch.
On off, defended off the front foot towards cover.
Good length delivery on off, Sharma defends it towards the off side.
Flighed delivery on middle, Pujara flicks this towards the square leg region for a brace. The fielder runs after it and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.

SIX! What a shot from Pujara! You don't see that too often from Pujara! Piedt bowls a rank long-hop on off, Pujara rocks back and pulls it with disdain towards deep mid-wicket. The ball flew deep into the stands.
The batsman gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Loopy ball outside off, Pujara pads this one.
Full delivery outside off, Rohit drives this towards the point fielder for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Rohit comes down the track and defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to the one of the short mid-wicket fielders.
FOUR! Nicely played from Pujara! Short ball outside off, Pujara camps back and guides this uppishly past the diving point fielder and into the fence.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara defends this towards the cover fielder.
Fullish delivery on middle, Cheteshwar defends it off the front foot towards the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone to the keeper.
Kagiso Rabada comes back into the attack! He has figures of 3-2-1-0.
Shortish outside off, Sharma looks to cut but is beaten.

NOT OUT AND IT IS A SIX! What a brilliant effort by Muthusamy but his toe has just touched the boundary cushion! Floated on middle and off, Sharma comes down the track and heaves it towards long on. Senuran Muthusamy who is standing there catches the ball. However, he loses his balance while taking the catch and throws it up in the air. He crosses the boundary line and comes back in to complete the catch. He is quite confident that he has taken the catch cleanly but the umpires want to get it checked. They go to the third umpire upstairs and the replays roll in. It shows that the toe end of Muthusamy's boot is touching the boundary cushion while he has the ball in his hand. An element of T20 cricket in this but unfortunately for the debutant, it does not bear fruit.
What a catch from Muthusamy! But is it clean? The umpires have gone on to check whether Senuran has touched the ropes or not. It looks close to the naked eye but let's see what happens.
Sharma has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the pads of Pujara, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Pujara defends this one off the front foot presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on middle and leg, Pujara pushes this one towards mid on for a single.
Flatter one on middle and off, Sharma tries to block it but the ball goes off the inside edge and thuds onto the pads.
Good ball by Maharaj! This one pitches and turns away from Sharma as he looks to block it out. He is beaten all ends up.
Another shorter one, Pujara cuts this one towards point and takes a single.

FOUR! This time off the back foot and Pujara is smashing it to all parts of the ground. Shortish this time outside off, Pujara rocks onto the back foot and cuts this one towards backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! Pujara on the attack now! He comes down the track and flicks this one towards backward square leg for a boundary.
Slower one from Maharaj, Pujara defends it onto the pitch.
Rohit comes onto the front foot and blocks this one towards the off side.
Sharma gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks this one out.
Darted on the boots, pushed again to the man at mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, pushed to the man at mid-wicket.
On the pads this time, Rohit blocks this one towards short leg.
Flatter on middle and off, blocked out by Sharma.
Flighted ball on off, Pujara defends it out.
Loopy ball on off, Pujara attempts to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Magnificent from Pujara! Another flighted ball outside off, Pujara once again comes down the track and drives this nicely through covers for a boundary.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
FOUR! Good shot from Pujara! He is looking to up the ante now, flighted ball on middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it beautifully towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.

FIFTY! Another excellent knock from Rohit! After a century in the first innings, continues it with a fifty in the second. He is having an excellent Test match. Full delivery on middle, Rohit flicks it towards long on for a single. Rohit has made full use of the opportunity. 11th fifty for him in Tests.
CP rocks onto the backfoot and punches the ball.
Pujara again looks to flick but this time misses to get hit on the pads.
FOUR! On the pads this time, Pujara flicks this one confidently off his pads towards square leg for a boundary.

EDGED AND FOUR! Chance of a catch but missed by de Kock. Shortish delivery by Piedt, Pujara comes down the track and tries to heave it over mid-wicket. He misses the ball and goes straight through to de Kock who misses it too as the ball races to the fine leg fence. The Ultra Edge comes into play and shows there was a faint edge on that one. Had de Kock held onto it, Pujara would have had to walk back to the pavilion.
Flatter on middle and off, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
On the pads this time, Rohit flicks it down towards fine leg and takes a single. Moves to 49.
Short ball outside off, Rohit cuts it towards the point region for a single.

OHH! What happened there? It was a flighted delivery around off, Rohit comes down the track in an attempt to defend it but there was a lot of spin on it and beats Sharma completely. Luckily for him, the spin takes the ball past the keeper and the first slip fielder towards short third man. No damage done.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman.
Flighted delivery outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Short ball on middle, Sharma pushes it to the cover fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit defends it back to the bowler.

DRINKS! This is the first Drinks break of the session. There will be another Drinks break in this session as this is an extended one. This has been a pretty quiet hour with not many events except for the dropped catch of Cheteshwar Pujara. The scoring rate has been quite low and both the sides will be relatively happy with it. Maharaj to continue following the Drinks break with the Hitman on strike. He is on 47 and will be looking to get to his half century quickly.
Looped up ball on off, Cheteshwar comes down the track and looks to defend but it goes off the pads towards the off side.
Flighted ball on middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara charges down the track and pushes it uppishly towards the man at mid on.
Flat delivery around middle, RS flicks it to square leg for a single.
Quicker delivery on off, Sharma comes down the track and defends it out.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Rohit flicks it towards the leg side.

Pujara has asked for a change of gloves due to the humid weather out there. Also, Pujara and Rohit have sent a message to their captain, Virat Kohli via Kuldeep Yadav who has communicated the same. The players gather around to listen to it in the dressing room. Any guesses on what the message was?
Full delivery on middle, CP defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
On off, defended it off the front foot towards the off side.
Flatter delivery on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma sweeps it in front of square leg for another single.
Flighted ball outside off, Rohit pushes it towards the point fielder.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Short ball outside off, Pujara pushes this towards the off side.
On off, defended off the front foot by Pujara.
Pujara works this one towards the man at mid-wicket.

CHANCE! Flighted delivery on off, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it towards short leg where Markram is hit flush on the left knee. Can't be called a dropped catch as Aiden did not manage to put a hand on it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
A Steven Smithesque leave by Rohit Sharma! Outside off, Sharma leaves the ball and then brings the bat down from behind. Looks like a modern day technique now.
FOUR! Deft touch by Rohit! Outside off, shortish, Rohit opens the face of his bat and guides this towards the third man fence for a boundary.
BEATEN AGAIN! Floated outside off again, Sharma goes for the sweep but misses the ball completely.
Sharma gets right behind the line of the delivery and blocks it out.
BEATEN! Floated outside off, the ball skids on after pitching. Sharma looks to play at it but is beaten as he does so inside the line.
Keshav Maharaj is back into the attack.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara flicks it towards the leg side.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

DROPPED! De Kock is the culprit! Piedt bowls a quicker delivery through the air around off, Pujara looks to defend but gets an edge towards the keeper who fails to hold on to it. It was a tough catch as it was going quickly. Dane Piedt had almost started celebrating but to his disappointment, the catch was dropped by de Kock.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Pujara comes on the front foot and blocks this one.
Flatter on middle and off, Rohit tries to block it but it rolls off his gloves towards square leg and the batters take one.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara lets this ball go to the keeper.

FOUR! First boundary for Pujara! Full delivery on the pads, Pujara finally flicks this nicely towards the square leg region for a boundary. Maharaj runs after it from square leg and does all the hard work before he parries it into the ropes while sliding forward. He tried to pull it back but is unable to do so. The fielder from deep square leg also was running in but does reach. 5500 runs for Pujara in Test matches with this boundary.
Good length on middle and leg, Pujara once again defends this towards the leg side.
On middle, defended off the back foot towards the man at silly mid on.
Back of a length delivery on middle, CP defends it off his back foot towards mid on.
Good length ball on off, Cheteshwar defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Short ball on off, Rohit pushes it to the off side. Good over for India.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit defends it out.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman.

FOUR! Excellent batting this! First a six and now a boundary. Bowls a flighted delivery outside off, Rohit plays a paddle sweep from outside off and plays it towards the fine leg region for a boundary.

SIX! Magnificent shot! Flighted ball on middle, Rohit comes down the track and lofts it straight over the bowler's head for a maximum. He is looking to upset the rhythm of Piedt here. He has now hit the most sixes by an Indian in a single Test match. Hitman on fire!
Full delivery on off, Sharma flicks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Fullish delivery outside off, Pujara defends it towards the off side. Going has been tough for India as only seven runs have come off five overs so far.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Pujara defends it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
On a length outside off angling away, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball around off angling into the stumps, Pujara defends it out off his front foot towards silly mid on.
Good length delivery on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it towards short mid-wicket.

Very interesting field set. There are three fielders in catching positions, a slip fielder staying very wide from the keeper, a short mid-wicket and a silly mid on. Looks like there is a plan in place here for Pujara!
Full delivery on middle, Pujara defends it towards bowler.

BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Piedt! Bowls a flatter delivery outside off, Rohit attempts to defend it but fails to put any bat on it. There was extra bounce on that one. Piedt has looked better so far than what he bowled in the first innings.
Loopy ball on off, Rohit pushes it towards point.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle with little extra bounce, Rohit defends it to short leg.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted ball outside off, Rohit attempts to defend but gets an edge past the first slip fielder towards the third man region for a couple.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it towards the leg side.
Another full delivery on middle, Cheteshwar pushes it back to Philander.
On middle, defended off the front foot back to the bowler by Pujara.
Another full delivery outside off, CP drives this towards the mid off fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara defends it towards the leg side.
The South African skipper, Faf du Plessis is seen having a word with the umpires. Not sure what the conversation is all about.
Short delivery outside off, Pujara cuts it towards the cover region and will keep the strike for the next over.
Full delivery on middle, Rohit plays a slog sweep towards the square leg region and takes another single.
Another full delivery outside off, Pujara comes down the track to push it to cover but gets an outside edge towards short third man for a single.
Fullish delivery on middle, Pujara dances down the track and pushes this towards mid on.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery around off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it to cover.
Dane Piedt to bowl from the other end. This is the first time that the off spinner has come on in this innings.
Good length delivery on middle, Rohit flicks it towards the leg side.

Good length delivery on off, Rohit puts on his dancing shoes and looks to clear the long off fence but does not time it well enough. The fielder from mid off runs after it to take the catch but it falls well ahead of him. The batters take two.
On a length on off, Sharma pushes this to the fielder at cover again.
Another full delivery outside off, Rohit drives this again towards cover.
Full delivery on off, Rohit drives this towards the cover region.
Starts with a good length ball on middle, Sharma defends it towards the leg side.

The second session is ready to begin! Rohit Sharma and Cheteshwar Pujara are making their way out to the middle along with the South African players. Rohit Sharma will be on strike to Vernon Philander. This is an extended session again to make up for the loss of overs on Day 1.
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

The visitors were good with the ball and bowled probing lines and lengths which troubled the batsmen. Maharaj was the pick of the bowlers and was rewarded with the wicket of Agarwal. Still a lot of time to go in this Test match and it will be interesting to see what happens after the Lunch break. Join us at 1210 local (0640 GMT) for another engrossing session!

A session which has belonged to both the sides! The last two wickets of South Africa added valuable runs as they squeezed India's lead to 71 runs. When the hosts came out to bat, Mayank was not in the same rhythm as he was in the first innings and struggled to get off the mark before being dismissed off the bowling of Keshav Maharaj.
Fuller one on the pads, it keeps a bit low. Pujara clips it in front of square leg and takes a couple. LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Again outside off, Pujara keeps his bat behind his pad and lets it through to de Kock.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
This one is again outside off, it is a touch short and sticks on the surface. Sharma rocks back and uppishly plays it towards cover-point for a single.
A touch wide, Sharma opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man.
Floated one just outside off, Sharma blocks this one towards the off side.
Fuller and on off, Pujara pushes this one towards cover.
Length ball outside off, Pujara looks to defend but it goes off the bottom half of his bat towards second slip.
Fuller this time, Pujara pushes this one towards cover-point.
Length ball on middle and leg, Pujara pushes it back towards mid-wicket.

Slight confusion there but no worries! On the pads of Pujara, he flicks it towards square leg. Rohit thinks of a run, he sets off but is sent back. A slight fumble from the fielder and thus no harm done.
Length ball on middle and leg, pushed by Pujara towards cover.
SIX! Flat one over the fence! Maharaj bowls this a touch short, Sharma rocks onto the back foot and pulls it powerfully over mid-wicket for a maximum.
Another one outside off, Sharma again leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Rohit.
On the pads this time, Sharma flicks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a couple. A huge roar from the crowd.
Strange fielding position now! Gets a leg slip.
This time on middle and leg, pushes this one back to the bowler.
Floated one outside off, Rohit pushes this towards cover.
Length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on this time.
Again on a length, Pujara pushes this one off the back foot towards mid off.
Pujara plays this one off the back foot towards the off side.
Another length ball, this time on middle. Pujara pushes this back to the bowler.
Length ball outside off, defended towards the point region.
Length ball just outside off, Sharma pushes this one towards cover-point and takes a single.
Pujara plays that off the front foot onto the pitch.
Fuller this time, flatter too. Pujara blocks this one towards the off side.
Short of a length ball just outside off, Pujara rocks back and cuts it towards point but straight to the man.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Floated on the leg pole line again, Pujara blocks this one towards long on.
Floated on the leg pole line, Rohit pushes this one towards long on for a single. Keshav Maharaj dives to his right in an attempt to stop it but fails to do so.
Good length ball on middle and off, jagging back in. Pujara does well to defend it out off the front foot.
On the pads, Rohit looks to flick this one but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
Fullish delivery on middle, Rohit defends it off the front foot towards the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Rohit tries to cut but it goes off the inside half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
On a length outside off, Rohit is on his back foot and guides this one towards the backward point region.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Rohit flicks it towards the leg side.
Cheteshwar Pujara is the new man in! He did not make much of an impact in the first innings. Can he make it here? Kagiso Rabada comes into the attack as well.

OUT! CAUGHT! The double centurion of the last innings is out of here! Brilliant bowling from Keshav Maharaj this, bowls it slower through the air. There is a lot more spin as a result. It pitches and turns away from the blade of Mayank as he looks to defend it. It goes off the outside edge towards first slip where Faf du Plessis, the skipper makes no mistake. Agarwal has to walk back much earlier in this innings and India are effectively 92/1.
FOUR! Outside the off pole line, Agarwal paddles this one although with his eyes closed. The ball goes of the bat towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Agarwal defends this one well onto the ground.
Floated on middle and off, Agarwal pushes this one towards the off side.
Mayank has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

EDGED BUT SAFE! The ball spinning a lot more than usual now. Floated on the middle stump line, it pitches and straightens. Rohit looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards third man for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Agarwal drives this nicely towards the bowler who fields it well.
Fullish delivery on middle, Agarwal lunges forward and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length on middle, Agarwal defends it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Mayank defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on the pads, Mayank flicks it towards the backward square leg region for a couple. Muthusamy runs to his right and cleans it up. First runs off the bowling of Philander in this innings.
On a length outside off which kept a little low, Agarwal gets his bat down in time and guides it towards point.

SIX! Slog sweeps this one with ease! Floated outside off, Rohit gets down on one knee and just slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum. No fielder there so a safe shot as well. This is now the most sixes which has been hit in India. 21 sixes so far.
Rohit Sharma has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

NOT OUT! It looked close at the start due to the confidence shown by de Kock but Sharma's foot is well in. Good delivery this one by Maharaj. He floats it up, inviting Sharma for the drive. He obliges and takes a step forward but misses the ball. De Kock gathers it and is quick to remove the bails. He is confident that he has got his man. The decision is referred to the third umpire. The replays roll in and shows that the back foot of Rohit is in.
Review time! A stumping appeal is taken upstairs with Rohit Sharma being the man in question! De Kock looks confident. Let's see what happens.
Short leg fielder is put on the off side near the gully region!
Full and outside off, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover and takes a single.
Another one tossed up just outside off, Agarwal tries to push at this one but gets a soft inside edge on this one which goes to the first slip fielder on the bounce.
Floated one, full and on the off pole. Rohit drives this one towards long off and takes a single.
Length ball on off, pushed towards mid off. 18 balls in and Agarwal is yet to get off the mark which means three consecutive maidens for Philander as well.
Philander goes fuller now, Agarwal pushes this one towards cover.
Good length delivery outside off, Agarwal cuts it well but straight to the man at backward point.
On the pads this time, Agarwal clips this towards mid-wicket.
A touch short, near  the hips of Agarwal. He pushes this one towards mid on.
Length delivery around off, Agarwal does well to block it out.
Sharma defends the last ball of the over onto the turf.
Another one outside off, turning in but left alone by Rohit.
Sharma defends this one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, spinning in, left alone by Sharma.

Misfield! Not what the bowler wants! Back of a length outside off, Sharma cuts this one towards backward point. De Bruyn is lazy to get down and the ball sneaks through him as the batters take a couple.
Floated outside off, Sharma drives this towards cover but the fielder at cover dives low down to his left and does well to stop it.
Good length ball on middle and off, Mayank taps it onto the pitch as the ball rolls towards the cover region.
Philander bowling his usual length deliveries, Agarwal stands tall and defends it out.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards cover.
Length ball outside off, Mayank tries to block it but it goes off the bottom half of his bat past the wickets.
This time Mayank gets behind the line of this length delivery and blocks it out.
Beaten! Length ball just outside off, Agarwal looks to play at it but the away movement on this one beats the outside edge of Mayank's bat as he is completely squared up.
Defended off the front foot by Rohit Sharma presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! India and Rohit  are underway in spectacular fashion! Maharaj bowls this one shorter and outside off, Rohit rocks back onto the back foot and pulls this through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Sharma has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, Rohit defends this one towards the off side.
Another one pushed flatter outside off, Rohit pushes it out onto the pitch.
Flatter one to start off by Maharaj, Rohit blocks it out.
Spin will play a crucial part in this innings as the pitch is taking a lot of turn and India will have to play spinners well.
Keshav Maharaj will share the new ball with Philander!
Good length delivery on middle, Agarwal defends it out. Good start from Vernon Philander as it is a maiden.
BEATEN! Good delivery from Philander! Bowls it on a length around off, Mayank attempts to defend it but it beats the bat of Agarwal and goes to the keeper.
On a length on off, Mayank rocks on his back foot and defends it towards mid off.
Fullish length on off, Mayank defends it off the back foot towards the off side for a single.

160 then. Points for India in the World Test Championship so far. This being a 3-match series, a win gives you 40 points. Way ahead of the rest and given that they are enjoying a home run for a lengthy period of time, the hosts would like to consolidate that spot in the coming months. What about South Africa? They fought hard for the first 3 days but Day 4 was probably where the game slipped away. There are some technical shortcomings as well, along with the weather conditions. But they need to find answers to all these pretty quickly, as the second Test is upon all from Thursday, 10th October, 2019 from 9.30 am local (0400 GMT) in Pune. Would winning the toss make things any better? Doubt that, with India playing so well but Faf du Plessis can perhaps consult Australian Women's captain, Meg Lanning to help win the toss. ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

ROHIT SHARMA HAS BEEN NAMED THE MAN OF THE MATCH. Says that he just wanted to go out there and do what he does best, exploring opportunities at the top. Thanks the coach and management for giving him that chance. Believes that getting 40 points is more important than all that and is happy that India continue to stay at the top of the table in the World Test Championship. On him now opening in all formats, Rohit says that it was communicated to him around 2 years ago, that he might be asked to open, so it was not altogether a surprise and he used to practice really hard in the nets. On him playing watchfully at the start in both white-ball and red-ball cricket, Sharma says that one needs to assess the conditions first and then play your own game. Stresses that the batsman should be leaving the ball outside off, play as close to the ball as possible and then play one's shots, which has been his mantra so far. On being asked about him creating the record for hitting the most number of sixes in a Test, Rohit instantly says that there are quite a few things in Test cricket that he is not aware of. Adds that his main aim was to maintain his focus and outwit the bowlers, who, he believes are very smart these days.

Victorious Indian captain, Virat Kohli, comes up next. On being asked for the win, which was not easy, Kohli admits that it was so. Adds that they did get the result they wanted but admires the resistance shown by South Africa. Details that once you get 500 on the board, you are always in the ascending seat irrespective of the fight shown by the opposition. Praises his batsmen in both innings for scoring quickly and says that it was a tough grind, but due to the weather. On the pacers doing well on a track suited to the spinners, Kohli says that it all depends on the attitude. Adds that in the last 2 years, every Indian pacer has looked to contribute on every pitch, albeit bowling shorter spells and communicating well with the captain, even when conditions are difficult. Praises Ashwin and Jadeja for bowling consistently well, on a flat track in the first innings, with the offie taking 7 there and Jadeja taking quick wickets in the second. On Shami's spell this morning, Kohli feels that the pacer has always done well in the recent past and when the ball reverses, he is unstoppable. In the end, praises all the bowlers. On the current quality of the SG ball, Kohli feels that this particular lot is better than the previous one, staying hard for around 40-45 overs but wants it to be harder till at least 60 overs because, even if the pitch is helping you, you would want the ball to do something as well.

Time for the presentation. Faf du Plessis first up, the South African captain. A bit of a disgruntled look on his face. Praises India for putting up a great total and then his own team for fighting hard. Adds that in an ideal world, he would have loved his bowlers to bowl India out cheaply but has to stop and admire another Rohit special. Is wary of a pitch exploding on Day 5 but apart from the collapse on Sunday morning, he believes that South Africa fought hard. On the wicket for this Test, Faf says that it seemed to hold on a bit and apart from Shami taking a 5-fer on Day 5, the seamers barely got much purchase. Rues the fact that his spinners could not do much in the third innings, which is where the game drifted away. Admits that the collapse this morning was way too quick and it does happen on Day 5 but quickly says that one cannot do much about it, so wants to move forward and look ahead to the second Test.

Mohammed Shami is gifted the stump which he broke, while cleaning up Dane Piedt. On being asked his plan to bowl on the wicket, Shami says that it is very difficult to take wickets on such pitches, so the team planned to bowl in line of the stumps. On the pacers bowling well, Shami says that over the past 4-5 years, the combination of the pacers has been excellent and if the ball starts to reverse a bit, aided with uneven bounce, everyone does well. On breaking the middle order of the Proteas, Shami says that the aim is always to remove the top 5 of the opposition early and in doing that, keep the line which attacks the stumps. Thanks the crowd for its support.

The Indians then. Heroes? Oh you could make movies which could run successfully for the next decade. Rohit Sharma showing that he loves to open in any format. Just 176. 224 less perhaps? Then Mayank Agarwal. Getting to his double ton. The duo staging a 317-run opening stand. Then Ashwin taking a 7-fer, showing that he is still India's number 1 Test spinner. And Rohit again in the second dig, scoring his second century in this Test. And in the final innings, Jadeja and the second innings hero, Mohammed Shami. A total team effort. Simply superb. Given that a seamer has taken 5 wickets on Day 5, simply shows how good India's pace attack is even now. Here is the hero, talking to Sanjay Manjrekar.

Now, to this match overall. How many heroes for the South Africans? Maharaj in the first innings. For believing in himself while getting sent to the cleaners for two days that eventually he will get some reward, ending up with 3 scalps. Then Dean Elgar, Quinton de Kock and Faf du Plessis, for ensuring that there is some fight shown and the Proteas do not cave in. Made India bowl 131.2 overs, an achievement in itself, playing spin really well. But that was it. That seemed to take a heavy toll as they simply could not turn up with either bat or ball in the second innings. A lead of 71 was not what India would have expected after scoring 502/7 but the Saffas could not pounce on that opportunity.

India knew they had the aces when they came out to bowl this morning, only having to land the ball in the right areas and allow the pitch to do the rest. South Africa, inexperienced as they were, seemed confused as to whether they should come forward or stay back and were caught in no man's land. Markram was the only man to fight at the top while Muthusamy and Piedt averted some embarrassment with a 91-run stand lower down the order.

So how do you play low bounce and extra bounce? Difficult, very difficult. Probably go forward, rather than backward? And do not leave any ball. ANY. De Bruyn, Bavuma, de Kock and Piedt - all suffered the harsh consequences of the ball staying low while du Plessis chose to leave one and had to leave the field. Though the Proteas might look at that period of the first hour on the final day and call it a manic hour, it would still have been difficult for them or any team to hang around against a quality opposition on a wearing pitch. And that is why life is heaven for spinners in India on Day 5, seeming like hell in the first 3.

Right then. Took a while to come, after a collapse this morning, but eventually, India have won convincingly, with more than a session to spare. For all the fight shown by South Africa in the first innings, sadly, the second dig was a damp squib, though they can blame the inconsistent bounce on the pitch for the same.

The Indian players step out onto the field with one clear objective in mind - rip through the batting lineup of the visitors and bag the victory. One has to be brave to bet against them from doing so as well. The South African batters, Theunis de Bruyn and Aiden Markram are also out in the centre. Markram will take strike as Mohammed Shami starts the proceedings for India.

Hello and a warm welcome to our coverage of the final day of the Test match between India and South Africa! Day 4 saw India going way ahead in the game setting a target of 395 runs for the Proteas. Although one might question Kohli's decision to delay the declaration, the hosts will feel that they still have enough time in hand to bowl out the visitors. The spin duo of Ravindra Jadeja and Ravichandran Ashwin hold the key for the Indians to get a win in this game. The Proteas, on the other hand, again will need to bat out of their skins in order to even secure a draw. They have already lost the wicket of Dean Elgar which is a big blow but would hope for the rest of the batsmen to do the job. They would take heart from the fact that they have never lost a game in India after scoring 400-plus runs  in an innings. There is a hint of rain predicted throughout the day which the South Africans won't mind one bit but it is sunny at the moment. An enthralling final day awaits us. Stay with us for all the action from Visakhapatnam.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...

Now then, an exciting 5th day awaits. South Africa will be looking to play for a draw whereas India will be eyeing a win. 9 wickets is what they need and South Africa will probably have to bat out 98 overs. However, there are chances of rain and the visitors won't mind that at all. Do not miss the action which begins at 0930 local (0400 GMT). Till then, take care and goodbye!

Cheteshwar Pujara who is down for an interview says it is a tough pitch when you start your innings and he was finding it difficult to rotate the strike and accelerate but it worked out well in the end. Mentions once he got used to the pace, he knew what shots to play. States it wasn't easy but he needed to adjust. On him playing just one format, Pujara replies that it allows him to improve his fitness but sometimes he is not at his best because of the lack of match practice. Further adds they do have enough runs on the board and also have enough time. Ends by saying the wicket is not easy as there is variable bounce for the pacers and the spinners.

The only time the Indians might have been frustrated on Day 4 was probably when the last pair of South Africa managed to add some handy runs. However, once the last man was dismissed, it was all India. Courtesy Rohit's ton and handy contributions from others, they managed to set a massive target for the visitors. They declared with 13 overs to go in the day, all the overs left weren't possible but India did get a wicket in it.

A huge smile on the Indian players' faces as they make their way back to the pavilion. High fives all around as they head back. It has been their day without a doubt. Not only have they batted South Africa out of the game but have also got the big, big wicket of Dean Elgar in the 9 overs they have bowled.
